The paper deals with the application of deep learning for traffic sign detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of multi-scale convolutional neural networks and deconvolution sub-networks also suggests that the paper may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the practical application of the proposed method for autonomous driving, which may also fall under the robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques for traffic sign detection suggests that the paper may also fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) category.
